commit.message:
Change some Edebug specifications to ‘sexp’ to not evaluate them.

Edebug doesn’t handle bodies rewritten by generator.el well,
cf. https://debbugs.gnu.org/cgi/bugreport.cgi?bug=40434.  Until that is fixed,
it’s better to avoid instrumented the bodies altogether to avoid spurious bugs.

Improve Edebug specifications

I’ve mostly copied them from ‘iter-defun’ and ‘lambda’.  The proposed
ones look more correct to me than the existing ones.

Closes #11.

Mention asynchronicity of aio-defuns in describe-function

Closes #10.

Add gotcha about dynamic state outside of aio-with-async

This might be obvious, but at least I was initially confused by it.

Closes #9.

Add font locking for asynchronous functions

This is modeled after the font locking setup for Emacs Lisp ‘defun’ etc.

Closes #8.
